<dl id="n54149a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54149a">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54149a"> 149(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> optative</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&laquo;Du point de vue linguistique, dit-il, la formule n&apos;a pas toujours la forme d&apos;une pri&egrave;re. Il en est beaucoup o&ugrave; le verbe n&apos;est pas &agrave; l&apos;<mark>optatif</mark>, ni &agrave; l&apos;imp&eacute;ratif, mais &agrave; l&apos;indicatif. <br><font color="green">["From a linguistic point of view," he says, "the formula is not always in the form of a prayer. There are many where the verb is not optional, not imperative, but indicative.]</font> <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 185f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
